HEADWORD: Incide
<hw>In*cide"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incidere</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>caedere</ets> to
cut. See <er>Concise</er>, and cf. <er>Incise</er>.]</ety> <def>To cut;
to separate and remove; to resolve or break up, as by medicines.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

